# Frontend Conventions

## Page structure

Tool pages live at `app/(tools)/<tool>/page.tsx`. Each is `"use client"` and follows this shape:

1. Fetch data with `useFetch<T>("/tool/endpoint")` (one-shot) or `usePoll<T>("/tool/endpoint", intervalMs)` (live).
2. Local state for selection, search query, view mode.
3. Render: toolbar header → content area → optional detail panel or sheet.

## Data fetching

| Hook | When |
|------|------|
| `useFetch` | Data loaded once on mount, with `refetch()` for manual refresh |
| `usePoll` | Live data (GPU status, download progress) — polls at `intervalMs` |

Both use `api<T>(path)` from `lib/api.ts`. Paths are relative to `/api/` (e.g. `"/control/models"`).

## Styling

- Use CSS custom properties via inline `style={{ }}` for all DGX Lab design tokens (`--background`, `--surface`, `--elevated`, `--border`, `--border-subtle`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-tertiary`, `--color-cyan`, etc.).
- Tailwind for layout, spacing, and typography sizing (`flex`, `gap-3`, `text-[13px]`, `font-mono`).
- No Tailwind color classes — all color through CSS vars.
- Monospace (`font-mono`) for data values, model IDs, file paths, metrics. Sans for labels, headings, navigation.

## Component patterns

- Sheets (`@workspace/ui` `Sheet`) for pull/create actions that slide in from the right.
- Detail panels as a `<aside>` with `--surface` background and left border.
- Status dots: 5-6px rounded div, cyan = complete/connected, blue = running (pulse), amber = warning, red = error.
- Dense tables: no `<table>` — use CSS grid with `grid-template-columns` for alignment.

## Sidebar

New tools go in `components/app-sidebar.tsx` in the `sections` array:

```typescript
{ href: "/tool", label: "Tool Name", icon: "◇" }
```

Optional tools add `optional: true` and `settingsKey: "tool-key"`.
